      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "POURING RAIN (4) won comfortably last time scoring by 4.5 lengths at this track after jumping from box 4 (17.51). Safe beginner but tricky box to overcome. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Sure to prove hard to beat. KINGSBRAE MAGGIE (3) is a talented type and proved too classy last time to win by 2.5 lengths at this track in a handy 17.63 beating Mum's On Fire. Has never been out of the placings from two starts out of this box. Likely to be in the finish. QUEEN LOCH (1) held a forward position from the pinch but began to paddle on the bend and drifted out of the finish when 8th at The Gardens in Grade 5 company. Solid record here at this trip including five wins. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Has ability and can atone. TIGRESS WINK (2) did a good job to finish third last time out over 300m at this track (17.86) in a Grade 4/5, the second top-three finish on the trot.",
